      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(memory): scrub stale dreaming sessions on startup",
        "body": "Fixes #78458.\n\n## Root cause\n\nThe dreaming narrative cleanup path already scrubbed stale `dreaming-narrative-*` session rows after a normal narrative run. When the Gateway restarted while a narrative session was still in progress, that post-run cleanup path could be skipped. On the next startup, memory-core only reconciled the managed dreaming cron job, so aged interrupted dreaming sessions could remain in the session store and continue showing in the sidebar.\n\n## Fix\n\nReuse the existing bounded dreaming narrative scrubber from `gateway_start` after managed cron reconciliation is scheduled. Cleanup failures are caught and logged as warnings so startup stays alive. The scrubber itself keeps the existing guardrails: state-dir agent stores, safe session id handling, the orphan age threshold, and dreaming transcript marker checks before archiving orphan transcripts.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Gateway startup now reclaims aged interrupted `dreaming-narrative-*` session rows and archives the orphan transcript while preserving fresh dreaming sessions and non-dreaming sessions.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw checkout on macOS, Node v22.22.1, branch `ben/issue-78458-dreaming-startup-cleanup` rebased onto current `upstream/main`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```bash\nsource ~/.nvm/nvm.sh && nvm use 22.22.1 >/dev/null && node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/memory-core/src/dreaming-narrative.test.ts extensions/memory-core/src/dreaming.test.ts\ngit diff --check\n```\n\nEvidence after fix:\n\n```text\nTest Files  2 passed (2)\nTests  110 passed (110)\n[test] passed 1 Vitest shard\n```\n\n`git diff --check` completed with no output.\n\nObserved result after fix: The new regression seeds an aged `agent:main:dreaming-narrative-light-orphan` row before firing `gateway_start`; after startup, that row is gone, the stale transcript has been archived with `.deleted.<timestamp>`, and the fresh dreaming row plus normal session row remain.\n\nWhat was not tested: Full Gateway restart with a live UI/sidebar was not run locally; the proof is the focused memory-core startup hook and session-store behavior requested by the issue.\n\n## Security note\n\nDiff-scoped security review found no new attacker-controlled input, auth boundary change, or unbounded filesystem sink. The cleanup path continues to operate inside OpenClaw state/session-store helpers and only archives aged orphan dreaming transcripts that contain the dreaming run marker.\n",
